'en', 'pageNumber': 0, 'inputText': '________________________________ January 25, 2024 – Update: We are back on the air! January 21, 2024 Over the weekend we had a critical component of our transmitter fail. We are diligently working to resolve the issue; however, we must wait for the part to arrive. Hopefully we can be back on the air no later than Tuesday, January 23. We appreciate your understanding and invite you to continue listening to us via the internet stream on your favorite streaming service, or by clicking below: Thank you for any help you can give and ask you to pray for me and all those involved in this travesty of justice. To help Derek, please go to http://givesendgo.com/gunby FIRST RESPONDERS CHANGE APPROACH TO SPECIAL NEEDS IN AN EMERGENCY Anderson, SC (5 January 2023) – Anderson County Emergency Management is changing how they approach people with special needs in a life-threatening emergency. The Special Needs Registry gives first responder details about a person, and their condition, at their fingertips before ever responding to an emergency. Register yourself or someone you know with special needs by simply inputting their address, their disability and a few details about how best to interact with them. “We can now provide critical information to our first responders, allowing them to respond with all the vital information they need while enroute,” Josh Hawkins, Emergency Management Director said. The information goes directly to dispatch so first responders are better equipped to help you and your family as they’re en route to your home. REGISTER ONLINE OR BY MAIL: https://www.emd.andersonsheriff.org/snregistry ————————- Sales experience preferred. Please email resume to rick@waim.us ——————————————————————– Welcome to News Talk 1230 WAIM! We have a great lineup of conservative talk programming including Rush Limbaugh, Sean Hannity, and Mark Levin, all anchored by our local Rick Driver Show weekday mornings from 7-10am. On this site you will find access to our Trading Post, where individuals can list items for sale, find items they are looking for, and make announcements. Also listed are links to City, County, and State offices, and a pathway to WAIM.TV where we broadcast live Anderson County Council meetings as well as other official events of interest. Thank you for supporting Anderson’s most listened to local talk station! You must be logged in to post a comment. [Read more] [Read more]'}]
